> **How can we identify a rectangle?**
The point on the top-left corner and the point on te bottom-right corner.
```
For each possible top-left
  For each possible bottom-right
    Check if matrix is made of 1s
	  If valid, we calculate area and update maxArea
```

> **How can we check if matrix with top-left (i, j) and bottome-right(x, y) is made of 1s?**
> In Brute Force, we check each cells in matrix, that takes O(n^2) time complexity
> To optimize, we observe that, 
```
with (i, j) as  top-left, rectangle with (x, y) as bottom-right is valid if 
  matrix[x][y] is 1
  && rectangle with (x, y - 1) as bottom-right is valid
  && rectangle with (x - 1, y) as bottom-right is valid
```
> We build an array isValid to save states. That takes O(1) time complexity.
****
```
    public int maximalRectangle(char[][] matrix) {
        if (matrix.length == 0) return 0;

        int rows = matrix.length, cols = matrix[0].length, maxArea = 0;
        // For each point topleft
        for (int i = 0; i < rows; i++) {
            for (int j = 0; j < cols; j++) {
                // Construt isValid
                boolean[][] isValid = new boolean[rows][cols];
                // For each point bottom right 
                for (int x = i; x < rows; x++) {
                    for (int y = j; y < cols; y++) {
                        if (matrix[x][y] != '1') continue;
                        // Check if valid matrix
                        isValid[x][y] = true;
                        if (x > i) isValid[x][y] = isValid[x][y] && isValid[x - 1][y];
                        if (y > j) isValid[x][y] = isValid[x][y] && isValid[x][y - 1];
                        // If valid, calculate area and update max
                        if (isValid[x][y]) {
                            int area = (x - i + 1) * (y - j + 1);
                            maxArea = Math.max(maxArea, area);
                        }
                    }
                }
            }
        }
        return maxArea;
    }
