# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
A rectangle can be maximum in three cases:
1. Length=1 and Breadth=A positive Integer value.
2. Breadth=1 and Heigth=A positive Integer value.
3. Both Length and Breadth are positive Integer values.

# Approach
1. Initially create two arrays as length[][] and breadth[][](below they are considered as h[][] and b[][]).
2. By using DP find the maximum length and breadth for each in their respective arrays.
3. Find Max value from two arrays.
4. For case 3: Both Length and Breadth are positive Integer values.
5. create res[][]
6. res[i][j] will be fill as mentioned below in code.Find the max value.
7. Return max value.

